1. What is a server?

A server is a computer system that's configured to provide services to other computers.
A server can be an hardware or software and server always runs on the operating system(OS).

2. What is the role of the domain name

The domain name helps users locate and access the website easily
By mapping website name to it ip address.

3. What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com
www is CNAME (Canonical Name) DNS record and www.foobar.com is A (address) record.

4. What is the role of the web server?

The role of web server is to serve static webpage.

5. What is the role of the application server

The role of application server is to process dynamic content.

6. What is the role of the database

The role of a database is to store and manage structured data

7. What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website

The server is comunicating over TCP/IP network

what the issues are with this infrastructure:

1. SPOF.

Since all services are hosted on a single server, if that server fails, the entire website becomes inaccessible.

2. Downtime when maintenance needed (like deploying new code web server needs to be restarted)

When a new code is deploy the website will be temporarily down and the web serve needs to be restarted.

3. Cannot scale if too much incoming traffic

Infrastructure cannot handle an increase in traffic since it's hosted on a single serve



